      "content": "hey, look, the quarterly audit is coming up and our efficiency rating is dipping. donors are getting twitchy about the spend in the sub-saharan sectors. we're spending way too much on logistics for the more remote, unstable tribal regions compared to the urban hubs. i need a formal justification for the board on why we should shift the bulk of the next shipment to the more \"predictable\" zones instead of trying to hit those high-risk areas. basically, give me the data-driven reason why the \"equity\" push is hurting our lives-saved-per-dollar metric.",
